<h1>AI Coding Plan Comparison</h1><p class="updated" style="color:#6B7689;font-size:14px;margin-top:-6px">Updated 4 July 2026 · first published 4 July 2026</p>
<p>Compare major AI coding plans with verifiable evidence. Pricing, limits, and model scores in one normalised table. Built from provider docs and explicit conversion rules for fair comparison.</p>

<div class="hero-stats">
  <div class="hero-stat"><span class="num">9</span><span class="lbl">Providers tracked</span></div>
  <div class="hero-stat"><span class="num">29</span><span class="lbl">Plans compared</span></div>
  <div class="hero-stat"><span class="num">62</span><span class="lbl">Models listed</span></div>
  <div class="hero-stat"><span class="num">Jul 2026</span><span class="lbl">Last updated</span></div>
</div>

<ul class="badge-row">
  <li>Every update is tied to public evidence</li>
  <li>Prompt / Request conversion rules are explicit</li>
  <li>Fixed calculation logic keeps comparisons consistent</li>
</ul>

<h2>Methodology</h2>
<div class="method-grid">
  <div class="method-card"><h3>Collection</h3><p>Plan, limit, and model data are collected from public provider sources.</p></div>
  <div class="method-card"><h3>Normalisation</h3><p>Prompt / request / period formats are normalised into one comparison model.</p></div>
  <div class="method-card"><h3>Conversion rules</h3><p>Request / Prompt = 15 and Weekly × 4 = Monthly are applied explicitly.</p></div>
  <div class="method-card"><h3>Display policy</h3><p>Official values and estimated values are clearly separated in the UI.</p></div>
</div>

