<div class="footnotes">
  <p>Values not explicitly provided by providers are shown in <span class="est">gray</span>.</p>
  <p>Many providers limit either Prompt or Request quotas. We convert dynamically using the Request / Prompt rate control above (default: 15).</p>
  <p>If the highest official limit is weekly, monthly is estimated as Weekly × 4.</p>
  <p>Artificial Analysis Score is measured by <a href="https://artificialanalysis.ai" rel="noopener">artificialanalysis.ai</a>. See their site for details.</p>
  <p>Some links may include referral codes.</p>
  <p>Plan details can change frequently. Always verify the latest information on official provider pages.</p>
</div>

<h2>Practical Guide</h2>
<p class="guide-section" style="background:none;border:none;padding:0">How to choose a coding plan</p>
<p>Price alone is not enough. Match each plan to your working style first. Start with Agent policy, limit type, and contract horizon.</p>

<div class="guide-section">
  <h3>1) Check Agent policy first</h3>
  <p>Some providers or plans restrict Agent usage. If Agent workflows matter, verify terms and the Uses column (Coding / Agent) before subscribing.</p>
</div>
<div class="guide-section">
  <h3>2) Prompt limits vs Request limits</h3>
  <p>For manual chat-heavy usage, batching work into fewer turns often aligns better with Prompt-style limits. For automation and Agent-heavy workflows, backend request volume can grow quickly, so prioritise plans with sufficient Request headroom.</p>
</div>
<div class="guide-section">
  <h3>3) Prefer monthly, use annual when early terms are superior</h3>
  <p>Plan revisions and enrolment changes are increasingly common. Monthly gives flexibility, while annual can be effective when launch-period terms are clearly advantageous.</p>
</div>
<div class="guide-section">
  <h3>4) Speed (token/s) is a real productivity factor</h3>
  <p>With the same quota, slower responses still cost more working time. We plan to add token-per-second metrics in a future update.</p>
</div>

<h3>Additional checks worth adding</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Separate Provided from Estimate values (estimates can shift)</li>
  <li>Confirm same-class model availability (none means unavailable)</li>
  <li>Match reset cycle (5h / daily / monthly) to your actual usage window</li>
</ul>

